WEBVTT

00:01.752 --> 00:05.089
DRAGON:
In a land of myth and a time of magic,

00:05.173 --> 00:10.219
the destiny of a great kingdom
rests on the shoulders of a young boy.

00:10.303 --> 00:13.055
His name, Merlin.

00:27.904 --> 00:30.865
| hope your trip isn't too upsetting.

00:30.948 --> 00:33.326
Thank you, Arthur.

00:33.409 --> 00:35.578
Ensure you return to Camelot
before dusk.

00:35.661 --> 00:37.038
Yes, sire.

00:55.848 --> 00:57.725
Where are they going?

00:59.518 --> 01:02.772
Morgana's on a pilgrimage
to her father's grave.

01:10.029 --> 01:11.405
You look troubled, Gwen.

01:12.740 --> 01:14.450
I'm fine.

01:15.159 --> 01:16.702
You're very secretive these days.

01:18.829 --> 01:21.290
I'm beginning to think
there's a man involved.

01:22.667 --> 01:25.378
When do I get to
meet any decent men?

01:32.760 --> 01:34.303
(MEN SHOUTING)

01:52.321 --> 01:55.157
My ladies, you must follow me...

02:11.799 --> 02:14.260
Gwen, head for the path. Go!

02:32.945 --> 02:35.948
| warn you.
| am Uther Pendragon's ward.

02:36.032 --> 02:39.076
He will have your heads
if any harm comes to me.

02:39.160 --> 02:42.121
| have no intention of harming you,
at least not yet.

02:45.708 --> 02:48.419
You're much more valuable
to me alive,

02:48.961 --> 02:50.463
Lady Morgana.

03:28.292 --> 03:31.045
He's coming.
You know what you must do?

03:36.258 --> 03:38.469
| trust you are comfortable?

03:38.552 --> 03:40.304
| demand to know
where you are taking us.

03:40.388 --> 03:42.515
You'll find out soon enough.

03:42.598 --> 03:45.601
We have a long journey ahead of us.
Get some rest.

03:50.648 --> 03:52.316
| wish to bathe.

03:53.818 --> 03:55.945
You wish to bathe?

03:56.028 --> 03:59.490
| am the King's ward and accustomed
to certain standards.

03:59.573 --> 04:03.786
I'm sure you are quite contented
to stink like a pig, but I am not.

04:04.745 --> 04:06.872
The Lady Morgana wishes to bathe.

04:09.417 --> 04:11.043
Who wants to help me guard her?

04:11.127 --> 04:12.670
(ALL LAUGHING)

04:14.922 --> 04:16.798
Morgana's party hasn't
returned to Camelot.

04:16.882 --> 04:18.426
There's no sign of her anywhere.

04:19.385 --> 04:21.178
Send riders to the outlying villages.

04:21.846 --> 04:23.931
| want every guard,
every sentry looking for her.

04:24.014 --> 04:25.850
| will dispatch them immediately.

04:31.564 --> 04:34.233
You may find the water a little icy.

04:35.693 --> 04:37.111
I'm sure I'll manage.

04:42.616 --> 04:44.994
If you were any kind of gentleman,
you'd give me some privacy.

04:45.327 --> 04:48.414
Well, unfortunately for you,
I'm no kind of gentleman.

04:48.998 --> 04:50.082
Now get on with it.

05:10.728 --> 05:11.979
You can at least turn your backs.

05:12.062 --> 05:14.273
So you can make a run for it?

05:14.356 --> 05:15.649
Do you think I'm that stupid?

05:15.733 --> 05:17.234
| think you're very stupid.

05:23.699 --> 05:25.493
(MAN SCREAMING)

05:26.076 --> 05:27.578
MORGANA: Run!

05:34.126 --> 05:36.045
No, no. This way.

05:49.058 --> 05:50.476
Come on.

05:50.559 --> 05:52.811
Put your arm around my shoulder.
Come on.

05:52.895 --> 05:57.316
No, no. We'll never out run them.
You must go on without me.

05:57.691 --> 06:00.110
-I'm not leaving you behind.
-Morgana. Go. Please.

06:00.194 --> 06:02.863
-You must get help.
-Take this.

06:03.364 --> 06:04.615
Go!

06:13.832 --> 06:15.417
(MAN SCREAMING)

06:26.470 --> 06:28.847
Check to see if anyone's alive.

06:34.186 --> 06:36.063
This is Mercian craftsmanship.

06:36.146 --> 06:37.481
Arthur...

06:45.155 --> 06:46.949
It's a ransom note.

06:47.616 --> 06:48.951
They've taken Morgana hostage.

06:51.120 --> 06:53.122
The tracks lead off this way.

07:13.267 --> 07:15.227
(LEAVES RUSTLING)

07:19.189 --> 07:20.524
(GASPING)

07:23.068 --> 07:24.361
Where's Guinevere?

07:30.075 --> 07:32.119
KENDRICK:
How could you let her escape?

07:34.246 --> 07:38.626
You bring me this servant.
She is worthless to us!

07:42.212 --> 07:43.964
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

07:48.385 --> 07:52.139
Here. Put them on.

07:53.432 --> 07:55.225
What are you going to do with me?

07:55.309 --> 07:57.895
Hengist has never met the Lady Morgana.

07:58.896 --> 08:02.232
For all he knows, you could be
Uther Pendragon's ward.

08:03.942 --> 08:05.736
| will not impersonate my mistress.

08:05.819 --> 08:06.987
(METAL CLINKING)

08:07.071 --> 08:09.239
Then you will die where you stand.

08:14.119 --> 08:15.537
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

08:15.621 --> 08:17.706
It is such a relief to see you safe.

08:17.790 --> 08:20.042
| was afraid someone would harm you.

08:20.125 --> 08:22.878
-The bandits still have Gwen.
-They were Mercian.

08:22.961 --> 08:26.090
We have heard that
Hengist has crossed the border.

08:26.173 --> 08:28.300
-Hengist?
-Then we must send a rescue party.

08:28.425 --> 08:31.887
If Hengist is holding her,
it would take an army to rescue her.

08:31.970 --> 08:36.225
-We can't abandon her.
-How many men do I send to save her?

08:36.308 --> 08:38.143
As many as it takes.

08:38.936 --> 08:41.772
Gwen gave herself up
so that I might escape.

08:42.272 --> 08:44.024
| owe her my life.

08:44.107 --> 08:46.610
She did so willingly
and she will be honored.

08:46.694 --> 08:49.822
| do not want her honored.
| want her rescued.

08:53.951 --> 08:56.286
She is more than just my maid.

08:58.205 --> 08:59.957
She is my friend.

09:01.959 --> 09:04.920
A servant is of no value
to these bandits.

09:05.003 --> 09:07.172
| fear she is dead already.

09:11.969 --> 09:13.178
No!

09:15.681 --> 09:17.683
We cannot give up hope.

09:21.353 --> 09:24.648
Arthur. I'm begging you.

09:26.150 --> 09:28.694
-You have to do something...
-My father's right.

09:28.819 --> 09:30.571
I'm afraid there's nothing we can do.

09:30.654 --> 09:32.531
How can you say that?

09:33.574 --> 09:36.076
How can you live with yourselves?

09:36.910 --> 09:38.328
All of you!

10:09.276 --> 10:11.195
Kendrick.

10:11.278 --> 10:13.363
| was beginning to think
you had failed me.

10:14.114 --> 10:17.034
May I present the Lady Morgana.

10:29.630 --> 10:30.714
Oh!

10:31.381 --> 10:34.718
You are as beautiful as they say,
Lady Morgana.

10:35.052 --> 10:37.596
| demand that you
release me immediately.

10:37.721 --> 10:41.433
Just as soon as Uther Pendragon
pays your ransom.

10:42.601 --> 10:43.977
In the meantime,

10:45.229 --> 10:47.022
you will be my guest.

10:47.105 --> 10:49.817
Do not flatter yourself.
| am not your guest.

10:49.900 --> 10:52.903
-I am your prisoner.
-As you wish,

10:55.280 --> 10:56.615
Take her to the dungeon.

11:04.790 --> 11:06.875
How can you be so heartless?

11:06.959 --> 11:09.002
Gwen is the most kind, loyal person
you'd ever meet.

11:09.086 --> 11:13.131
She's been more than a friend to us.
You'll leave her with those animals?

11:13.257 --> 11:15.759
-ARTHUR: Morgana...
-Have you no shame?

11:16.093 --> 11:18.053
-Do you only think of yourself?
-Morgana...

11:18.136 --> 11:22.057
| didn't know you were a gutless coward,
Arthur Pendragon.

11:22.140 --> 11:23.767
Morgana!

11:24.768 --> 11:27.729
Perhaps if you stopped shouting
at me for one second,

11:27.813 --> 11:30.440
you would notice that I am packing.

11:34.611 --> 11:36.947
-You're going after Gwen?
-Of course I'm going after her.

11:37.030 --> 11:40.200
What do you take me for? I couldn't
disagree with Father in public.

11:44.288 --> 11:45.789
Arthur...

11:47.332 --> 11:48.667
Bring her home.

11:55.132 --> 11:57.551
| suppose you and Arthur
are going after Gwen?

11:57.634 --> 12:00.804
Gaius. Don't even think
about telling me not to go.

12:00.888 --> 12:02.848
Nothing you can say will stop me.

12:02.973 --> 12:04.975
| wasn't going to try and stop you.

12:05.058 --> 12:08.228
All I ask is you make sure
you come back safely too.

12:25.329 --> 12:29.124
I'll fetch the horses.
You distract the guards.

12:29.374 --> 12:31.043
How do I do that?

12:31.501 --> 12:34.671
| don't know.
Do I have to think of everything?

12:41.637 --> 12:43.639
(CHANTING)

12:57.986 --> 12:59.029
(CHANTING)

12:59.529 --> 13:00.864
(BOTH EXCLAIMING)

13:05.369 --> 13:06.411
(CHANTING)

13:09.247 --> 13:10.666
(CRASHING)

13:15.545 --> 13:17.923
What did you do? I said distract them.

13:18.048 --> 13:19.841
Not knock them out.

13:21.051 --> 13:23.887
There's just no pleasing you sometimes.

13:31.436 --> 13:33.021
Silence!

13:35.774 --> 13:41.405
Our royal guest, Lady Morgana,
has grown bored.

13:42.072 --> 13:44.741
She needs entertaining.

13:45.242 --> 13:47.077
(ALL LAUGHING)

13:51.623 --> 13:53.083
(SHOUTING)

13:54.751 --> 13:56.920
(ALL CHEERING)

14:01.425 --> 14:02.926
Bring on the challenger!

14:24.281 --> 14:27.659
Only one of you will emerge
from the cage alive.

14:28.243 --> 14:29.786
Do you accept the challenge?

14:29.870 --> 14:31.413
(ALL CHEERING)

14:50.307 --> 14:52.059
(BOTH GRUNTING)

15:09.409 --> 15:10.786
(PANTING)

15:29.179 --> 15:31.348
-Kill!
-Kill! Kill!

16:03.839 --> 16:05.549
What's your name?

16:06.383 --> 16:08.301
My name is Lancelot.

16:08.385 --> 16:12.722
You have proved yourself
to be a skillful warrior.

16:14.182 --> 16:19.980
| believe you may even have impressed
our royal guest, Lady Morgana.

16:25.527 --> 16:26.820
My Lady.

16:31.408 --> 16:35.954
Next time you fight,
do not expect any mercy.

16:36.913 --> 16:38.540
Release the wilddeoren.

16:43.461 --> 16:44.546
No!

16:45.505 --> 16:47.340
(SQUEALING)

16:51.511 --> 16:53.096
(MAN SCREAMING)

17:11.156 --> 17:12.531
(CRASHING)

17:14.534 --> 17:16.619
What are you doing, Merlin?

17:18.204 --> 17:22.416
| must have fallen asleep.
I'm exhausted.

17:24.294 --> 17:27.255
| can barely keep my eyes open.

17:28.590 --> 17:30.842
Thank you. I feel so much better.

17:30.926 --> 17:35.055
Guinevere's life is at stake.
We can't afford to waste a second.

17:35.597 --> 17:36.806
(GROANS)

17:40.227 --> 17:42.229
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

17:45.899 --> 17:47.359
LANCELOT: Gwen.

17:50.695 --> 17:52.155
Lancelot.

17:52.239 --> 17:54.449
| couldn't believe my eyes
when I saw you.

17:54.532 --> 17:56.785
| thought my mind was deceiving me.

17:56.868 --> 17:59.204
Why does Hengist think
you are Lady Morgana?

18:00.330 --> 18:02.582
He believes he is holding
Morgana to ransom.

18:03.917 --> 18:06.294
When no ransom is paid,
he'll realize the truth,

18:06.378 --> 18:08.672
and then he will throw me
to those beasts.

18:08.755 --> 18:10.715
| will not allow that to happen.

18:12.175 --> 18:14.219
What are you doing here?

18:14.803 --> 18:16.680
Are you one of Hengist's men?

18:17.138 --> 18:18.223
No.

18:19.724 --> 18:22.644
What became of you
after you left Camelot?

18:23.395 --> 18:25.647
There are few opportunities
for men like me

18:25.730 --> 18:28.650
so I have been earning a living
the only way that I know,

18:29.317 --> 18:31.069
with a sword in my hand.

18:32.779 --> 18:35.907
It seems it is my destiny
to entertain men like Hengist.

18:36.533 --> 18:40.620
| don't believe that of you.
You were so full of hope.

18:41.871 --> 18:43.331
| was wrong.

18:44.165 --> 18:45.625
The world is not like that.

18:45.709 --> 18:47.502
| still see the hope in you.

18:48.670 --> 18:50.046
| do not accept it has gone.

19:00.223 --> 19:02.017
| have thought of you often.

19:03.601 --> 19:05.270
Have you thought of me at all?

19:08.440 --> 19:10.317
| thought I'd never see you again.

19:14.029 --> 19:15.405
(DOOR OPENING)

19:16.698 --> 19:18.783
Someone's coming.

19:18.867 --> 19:20.702
No matter what it takes,

19:20.785 --> 19:23.580
| will find a way
to get you out of here.

19:23.663 --> 19:24.914
| will.

19:31.629 --> 19:32.881
Merlin!

19:38.219 --> 19:39.929
What's happening?

19:42.015 --> 19:44.893
-How long was I asleep for?
-Long enough.

19:45.393 --> 19:48.313
-Did you get some rest?
- Icouldn't sleep.

19:51.691 --> 19:54.861
I've never seen you like this
about anyone.

19:55.487 --> 19:57.614
-What are you talking about?
-Gwen.

19:59.157 --> 20:01.368
You really care about her, don't you?

20:03.244 --> 20:06.456
What I care about is not wasting
any more time talking.

20:06.539 --> 20:08.249
Let's get moving.

20:19.719 --> 20:22.472
| have not yet received
word from Uther

20:22.847 --> 20:25.266
that he intends to pay your ransom.

20:27.894 --> 20:32.649
| was informed that the King
was extremely fond of his ward.

20:36.486 --> 20:39.823
Aren't you surprised he is content
to leave you here to die?

20:41.032 --> 20:44.244
How can I know the King's mind when
I'm locked in your stinking cell?

20:45.495 --> 20:50.208
If I do not hear from Uther
by dawn tomorrow,

20:51.584 --> 20:56.589
this stinking cell will be
the last place you ever see.

21:03.430 --> 21:05.181
(HENGIST LAUGHING)

21:07.267 --> 21:08.601
(EXHALES)

21:12.188 --> 21:15.984
The ransom is supposed to be
delivered to the Vale of Denaria.

21:16.067 --> 21:19.571
If they're holding Gwen anywhere,
it has to be there.

21:19.904 --> 21:23.741
Which means we can
save a day's riding

21:23.867 --> 21:27.954
if we cut through
the Tunnels of Andor.

21:36.629 --> 21:39.841
Oh, no. I know that face.
I'm not going to like this, am I?

21:39.924 --> 21:43.470
-What's in the tunnels?
-They're infested with wilddeoren.

21:44.053 --> 21:45.430
What're wilddeoren?

21:45.555 --> 21:47.265
They're like giant...

21:49.767 --> 21:52.896
-Baby rats.
-Baby rats?

21:53.730 --> 21:56.232
-They don't sound so bad.
-They feast on human flesh.

21:56.316 --> 21:58.067
Maybe we should go over the mountains.

22:02.906 --> 22:04.574
What're you doing?

22:04.657 --> 22:08.578
Wilddeoren are completely blind.
They hunt by sense of smell.

22:08.661 --> 22:11.247
Gaja berries will
put them off the scent.

22:11.331 --> 22:13.791
So if we smear ourselves with them,

22:13.917 --> 22:17.295
perhaps we can pass through
the tunnels undetected.

22:21.925 --> 22:24.344
Oh! These stink.

22:25.136 --> 22:26.471
They are really bad.

22:26.596 --> 22:28.598
Perhaps you would you prefer
to be eaten alive?

22:28.681 --> 22:29.807
Pass me some more, will you?

22:40.360 --> 22:42.445
(WILDDEORENS SCREECHING)

22:53.790 --> 22:56.626
- I just stood on something.
-That was my foot.

22:57.293 --> 22:58.545
Oh! Sorry.

23:06.177 --> 23:07.303
How much further is it?

23:07.387 --> 23:08.680
(SHUSHING)

23:16.145 --> 23:18.731
Wilddeoren. They're coming this way.

23:25.071 --> 23:29.158
Whatever happens, keep completely still.

23:31.035 --> 23:32.453
(SQUEALING)

23:40.962 --> 23:42.338
(SNIFFING)

23:55.685 --> 23:57.520
(BOTH SIGHING)

24:08.406 --> 24:09.991
LANCELOT: Gwen!

24:14.203 --> 24:15.788
Lancelot.

24:15.872 --> 24:18.207
| was terrified I might find
your cell empty.

24:18.291 --> 24:20.543
There has been no word from Uther.

24:20.627 --> 24:24.464
-Hengist is growing suspicious.
-You must keep up the pretense.

24:24.547 --> 24:26.424
| will not allow you to die here.

24:27.216 --> 24:28.885
What about you?

24:29.260 --> 24:30.720
| have little to live for.

24:30.928 --> 24:32.221
Do not say that.

24:33.222 --> 24:34.432
It is the truth.

24:35.183 --> 24:37.935
For all my words,
for all that I believed,

24:38.186 --> 24:40.229
| have come to nothing.

24:40.313 --> 24:42.982
You are everything that is right
with this world.

24:49.030 --> 24:51.532
| did not know you felt that way.

24:52.367 --> 24:57.622
| didn't even know I could
feel this way about someone.

25:01.167 --> 25:03.544
Then you have given me
a reason to live.

25:07.382 --> 25:08.424
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

25:08.508 --> 25:12.303
Be ready.
| will come for you before nightfall.

25:25.692 --> 25:27.527
The gaja berries worked.

25:30.780 --> 25:33.866
-You didn't know if they worked?
-Not for sure.

25:35.993 --> 25:37.120
Now you tell me?

25:38.037 --> 25:41.791
"What's that wilddeoren eating?"
â€œIt's all right. It's just Merlin."

25:42.917 --> 25:44.752
Are you trying to get us both killed?

25:45.002 --> 25:48.631
I'm sorry. I shouldn't have
risked your life like that.

25:50.925 --> 25:54.178
They do say love makes you
do strange things.

25:54.971 --> 25:57.098
What're you talking about?

25:57.682 --> 26:00.017
Why can't you just admit
your feelings for Gwen?

26:04.021 --> 26:06.983
It's so obvious.
A blind man could see it.

26:07.066 --> 26:09.736
Is it really that hard
to admit you like her?

26:09.819 --> 26:11.904
-Just say it.
-I can't!

26:14.198 --> 26:17.243
How can I admit that I think about
her all the time?

26:18.703 --> 26:22.290
Or that I care about her
more than anyone?

26:23.833 --> 26:27.545
How can I admit that
| don't know what I will do

26:27.628 --> 26:29.714
if any harm comes to her?

26:30.548 --> 26:31.758
Why can't you?

26:31.966 --> 26:34.927
Because nothing can ever
happen between us.

26:36.512 --> 26:39.098
To admit my feelings,
knowing that,

26:40.641 --> 26:42.977
it hurts too much.

26:46.230 --> 26:48.649
Who's to say nothing can happen?

26:49.233 --> 26:51.402
My father won't let me rescue a servant.

26:51.486 --> 26:53.821
Do you think he would let me marry one?

26:53.905 --> 26:57.241
-You want to marry Gwen?
-No. No. I don't know.

27:03.956 --> 27:07.043
It's all talk.
And that's all it ever can be.

27:09.962 --> 27:12.548
When you're king,
you can change that.

27:13.633 --> 27:16.260
| can't expect Guinevere to wait for me.

27:16.928 --> 27:20.723
If she feels as you do,
she'll wait for you.

27:25.645 --> 27:29.982
-We don't even know if she's alive.
-If she is, we will find her.

27:30.900 --> 27:32.944
Come on.
We've got a long trek ahead.

27:33.027 --> 27:35.112
Oh, and Merlin.

27:37.365 --> 27:41.452
If you dare tell anyone about this,

27:42.995 --> 27:47.250
| promise that I will make
your life a living hell.

27:48.584 --> 27:50.211
You mean more than you already do?

27:51.504 --> 27:52.672
Yeah.

27:56.425 --> 27:58.845
We could talk about your feelings
while you walk?

27:58.928 --> 28:00.596
Shut up, Merlin.

28:04.350 --> 28:07.562
Morgana. Morgana!

28:10.439 --> 28:12.692
| keep asking myself.

28:13.359 --> 28:17.321
Why does Uther not pay the ransom?

28:18.906 --> 28:20.616
He is a rich man.

28:21.659 --> 28:24.328
Why would he leave his beloved ward

28:25.413 --> 28:29.292
to suffer a slow and terrible death?

28:29.959 --> 28:31.377
| don't know.

28:32.628 --> 28:34.964
Please. Please...

28:35.172 --> 28:40.553
It must be very upsetting to know
that Uther has abandoned you.

28:40.845 --> 28:46.684
It seems that no one
in the world cares for you.

28:47.435 --> 28:51.689
| don't know why he doesn't pay.
Please. I don't know.

28:54.692 --> 28:56.277
Take her to her cell.

29:00.406 --> 29:02.283
Bring Kendrick to me.

29:02.867 --> 29:04.785
Perhaps he can tell me

29:05.453 --> 29:10.207
why the Lady Morgana has
the hands of a serving girl.

29:19.133 --> 29:20.468
(SOBBING)

30:15.272 --> 30:19.652
No! Wait!
Wait, Hengist. Hengist, wait.

30:23.197 --> 30:26.200
We did capture the Lady Morgana,

30:26.283 --> 30:28.619
but she escaped.

30:30.121 --> 30:32.415
So who exactly do I have in my dungeon?

30:34.625 --> 30:36.544
The Lady Morgana's maid.

30:41.465 --> 30:43.801
Thank you for being so honest.

30:45.386 --> 30:46.762
Release the wilddeoren.

30:46.846 --> 30:50.057
No! No! Please. I'm begging you!

30:50.391 --> 30:54.061
Hengist! Hengist, please!
Please, Hengist! Hengist!

31:04.739 --> 31:06.282
(DOOR OPENING)

31:09.326 --> 31:10.745
We haven't a moment to lose.

31:24.175 --> 31:25.551
(SHOUTING)

31:28.220 --> 31:29.764
(EXCLAIMING)

31:29.847 --> 31:33.726
Find her. Bring her to me alive.

31:37.938 --> 31:39.065
Follow this tunnel.

31:39.148 --> 31:41.192
It will take you out
beyond the castle walls.

31:41.275 --> 31:43.194
| will buy you as much time as I can.

31:44.195 --> 31:45.404
I'm not leaving you.

31:45.488 --> 31:46.530
You must.

31:46.614 --> 31:49.658
No. I will not leave you here to die.

31:49.742 --> 31:52.036
| would die for you
one hundred times over.

31:54.580 --> 31:56.248
Live for me.

31:57.166 --> 32:00.252
Or everything that I am
has been for nothing.

32:10.304 --> 32:13.474
As long as I live,
my feelings for you will never fade.

32:14.725 --> 32:18.270
Run. Don't stop running
until you are well away from here.

32:20.773 --> 32:23.400
Run. Run!

33:07.403 --> 33:08.988
(MAN SCREAMING)

33:23.127 --> 33:25.296
ARTHUR: We'll have to scale the walls.

33:26.797 --> 33:29.133
Maybe there's another way in.

33:29.216 --> 33:30.885
Why don't you go and
knock on the front gate?

33:30.968 --> 33:33.929
I'm sure if you ask nicely,
they'll hand Gwen over to you.

33:36.182 --> 33:37.600
(MEN LAUGHING)

33:43.230 --> 33:44.899
Before you die,

33:45.941 --> 33:49.778
| can promise you
the most unimaginable pain.

33:57.703 --> 34:00.206
You can do what you will with me.

34:01.457 --> 34:04.919
| do not care.
You can do no harm to Guinevere.

34:07.421 --> 34:09.130
Was that her name?

34:10.799 --> 34:12.134
A serving girl,

34:14.386 --> 34:18.431
and you really believe
she's worth dying for?

34:20.559 --> 34:23.978
She is worth more to me
than you will ever understand.

34:39.119 --> 34:41.288
You thought she'd got away?

34:41.746 --> 34:44.458
No, you failed her.

34:45.000 --> 34:49.463
And that must hurt you
more than I will ever understand.

34:49.545 --> 34:51.090
(ALL LAUGHING)

35:06.021 --> 35:07.523
(GRUNTING)

35:11.735 --> 35:14.905
You really are completely useless,
aren't you, Merlin?

35:17.199 --> 35:20.661
It's harder than it looks.

35:28.043 --> 35:30.337
Now you're just showing off.

35:37.636 --> 35:40.264
You distract them. I'll knock them out.

35:42.558 --> 35:44.268
How do I distract them?

35:53.235 --> 35:54.737
What are you doing there?

35:54.820 --> 35:55.946
Nothing.

36:00.075 --> 36:02.369
Actually, it's a funny story.

36:02.453 --> 36:04.705
| was out walking
and I took a wrong turn,

36:04.788 --> 36:06.498
and here I am.

36:07.082 --> 36:08.876
Do you know the way
to the Vale of Denaria?

36:09.126 --> 36:10.586
Who are you?

36:11.420 --> 36:12.463
Me?

36:12.546 --> 36:14.590
I'm no one.

36:16.550 --> 36:18.052
It's him you need to worry about.

36:18.135 --> 36:19.261
Who?

36:26.935 --> 36:28.687
That actually worked pretty well.

36:35.444 --> 36:37.279
What do you say?

36:38.155 --> 36:41.408
-Shall I spare them?
-(ALL LAUGHING)

36:41.492 --> 36:45.746
-Kill! Kill! Kill!
-Kill! Kill! Kill!

36:46.830 --> 36:49.083
I'm sorry. This is my fault.

36:49.166 --> 36:53.170
You have nothing to be sorry for.
You reminded me of who I am.

36:53.670 --> 36:57.341
| will die with faith in my heart.
That is worth more than anything.

37:05.474 --> 37:07.142
Release the wilddeoren.

37:07.226 --> 37:08.268
(ALL CHEERING)

37:14.191 --> 37:15.609
(SQUEALING)

37:37.047 --> 37:38.549
GWEN: Arthur!

37:45.889 --> 37:47.224
(ROARING)

37:50.018 --> 37:51.186
What're you doing here, Lancelot?

37:52.896 --> 37:55.357
| came to save Gwen.
What about you?

37:55.441 --> 37:56.775
Likewise.

38:00.070 --> 38:01.613
Get behind us!

38:09.163 --> 38:10.539
(CHANTING)

38:17.754 --> 38:19.631
The tunnel. It's our only chance.

38:19.715 --> 38:20.883
Merlin!

38:22.342 --> 38:24.553
Don't sit there cowering!
Let's go!

38:27.473 --> 38:28.682
After them!

38:38.484 --> 38:40.819
Take Guinevere. I'll hold them off.

38:40.903 --> 38:42.154
No!

38:43.238 --> 38:45.199
Guinevere! We have to go!

38:50.078 --> 38:51.455
(CHANTING)

38:54.791 --> 38:56.376
Open the gate!

38:58.837 --> 39:00.130
(SCREECHING)

39:06.011 --> 39:08.222
| see you're still up to
your old tricks, Merlin.

39:08.305 --> 39:11.225
Probably best you don't
tell anyone about that.

39:17.814 --> 39:19.233
(PANTING)

39:20.400 --> 39:23.278
It's good to see you both.
Where are your knights?

39:24.112 --> 39:25.322
It's just us.

39:29.535 --> 39:31.620
ARTHUR:
We've got to keep moving.

39:56.937 --> 39:59.940
Thank you, Arthur.
We owe you our lives.

40:19.751 --> 40:22.838
I'm surprised that you would
undertake such a rescue mission

40:24.172 --> 40:25.966
with just the two of you?

40:29.386 --> 40:32.472
My father would not risk the lives
of his knights for a servant.

40:33.140 --> 40:35.726
And yet you disobeyed him
and came here anyway?

40:40.272 --> 40:42.608
The truth is, I only came
because Morgana begged me.

40:50.741 --> 40:53.035
| think I will get some rest.

40:58.999 --> 41:00.834
We should all get some rest.

41:00.917 --> 41:02.961
| will stand guard for a while.

41:07.799 --> 41:10.886
I'll just sit here then.

41:23.940 --> 41:27.110
Is it true that Arthur
came to rescue Gwen

41:27.194 --> 41:30.155
because Morgana begged him?

41:36.745 --> 41:38.413
He has feelings for her, doesn't he?

41:43.168 --> 41:45.545
What about you?
Do you have feelings for Gwen?

41:47.839 --> 41:52.219
My feelings do not matter.
| will not come between them.

41:57.557 --> 41:59.017
Tell Gwen...

42:00.936 --> 42:03.563
Tell Gwen that she has
changed me forever,

42:05.232 --> 42:07.359
but some things cannot be.

42:25.001 --> 42:26.211
Where's Lancelot?

42:33.009 --> 42:34.219
Where is he?

42:35.595 --> 42:36.972
He's gone.

42:39.599 --> 42:40.851
No.

42:46.106 --> 42:48.233
He said that some things can't be.

42:51.069 --> 42:54.990
But he wanted you to know
that you have changed him forever.

43:17.012 --> 43:18.388
We have a long walk ahead of us.

43:55.467 --> 43:57.469
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

44:00.889 --> 44:02.182
Morgana.

44:04.976 --> 44:07.395
There's someone here to see you.

44:08.939 --> 44:10.106
Gwen.

44:13.527 --> 44:15.111
| thought I would never see you again.

44:41.054 --> 44:45.267
Look on the bright side.
You've still got me.

44:46.268 --> 44:48.603
-Is that supposed to cheer me up?
- I thought it might.

44:48.687 --> 44:51.648
You really are a complete idiot,
aren't you, Merlin?

44:52.440 --> 44:54.109
DRAGON: Merlin.

44:54.943 --> 44:57.529
The potion is prepared.

44:59.614 --> 45:02.617
GAIUS: The Lady Catrina
is not all she seems to be.

45:02.701 --> 45:06.037
Already he falls for me.
| can see it in his eyes.

45:06.872 --> 45:08.248
How could he
resist such beauty?

45:10.667 --> 45:11.751
(FARTING)

45:11.835 --> 45:14.004
You're going to tell Uther
that his new lady is a troll?

45:14.087 --> 45:16.131
That's exactly
what I'm going to do.
